						               													<description>By purchasing extra sets of marbles, Abalone can be played with 3-6 players, expanding the situations in which an otherwise two-player game could be brought to the table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Where two players each play with 14 pieces, expanding the game allows each of three players to use 11.  Or, with a fourth color, four players play in two teams, each player having 9 marbles.  A fifth color allows for an unusual five-player variant in which the four players who start at the edges each have 8 marbles, but the center player starts with 7, to compensate for the advantageous start position.  Finally, a sixth color permits six players to play in three teams, each player having 6 precious marbles.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In addition to these variants to accommodate varied numbers of players, the extra marbles can also enable numerous other variants to be played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
